  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Tuition Workflows**\n\nI\'m currently focused on dissecting the provided image and its implications for building this web application. The image details the daily workflow for handling tuition payments at Kim Academy. Step 1, \"Nh\341\272\255n th\303\264ng b\303\241o ti\341\273\201n,\" is the current area I\'m focusing on. I\'m aiming to translate this visual workflow into concrete functional requirements for the application.\n\n\n**Mapping Workflow to Functionality**\n\nI\'ve progressed past the initial notification stage and moved to mapping the subsequent steps in the tuition process. I\'m now translating \"Nh\341\272\255p d\341\273\257 li\341\273\207u\" and \"C\341\272\255p nh\341\272\255t file\" into specific database interactions and user interface components. I\'m focusing on how the system will manage both offline and online student data, including the complexities of GVNN (I\'ll need to research that further). Reconciling data and generating the end-of-day report are next on my list to model.\n\n\n**Defining Application Scope**\n\nI\'ve clarified the core features the application must provide based on the roles and steps described. I\'m focusing on user interactions: inputting transactions, viewing and managing them, filtering between offline/online data. I\'m also planning to create the daily report, and a section for the accountant to mark invoices. Regarding data storage, I\'m leaning toward using local storage for simplicity. I\'m also considering a single-view, single-screen dashboard structure.\n\n\n**Designing UI Elements**\n\nOkay, I\'m now structuring the user interface around tabs for \"Nh\341\272\255p li\341\273\207u\", \"Thu HP h\341\272\261ng ng\303\240y & \304\220\341\273\221i chi\341\272\277u\", \"B\303\241o c\303\241o cu\341\273\221i ng\303\240y\", and \"H\303\263a \304\221\306\241n (K\341\272\277 to\303\241n)\". For the input tab (\"Nh\341\272\255p kho\341\272\243n thu m\341\273\233i\"), I\'m designing a form with fields for date, student details, class, online/offline status, amount, payment method, term, and notes. The table is up next, allowing date-based filtering. The final daily report generation is also being sketched out. I am also planning on a way for the accountant to mark transactions as invoiced. Given the single-view constraint, these all have to work in one place.\n\n\n**Refining UI Structure**\n\nI\'m now revising the single-page dashboard concept. The plan involves a left pane for transaction input, a right or bottom pane displaying today\'s transactions, and a top-right button for the end-of-day report. I am designing a functional form using the data from the workflow, for date, student, class, type, term, amount, payment method, sender, notes, reconciled status, and invoiced status. I plan to use React, `lucide-react` icons, and Tailwind for development.\n\n\n**Structuring Data and UI**\n\nI\'m now diving into the implementation details. I\'m focusing on defining the data structures and UI components. The `metadata.json` file is next to be updated. I\'ll utilize `date-fns` for date formatting or maybe native Intl, and I\'ll create `src/types.ts` to define interfaces like `PaymentMethod`, `StudyType`, and `Transaction`. The core components (`TransactionForm`, `TransactionList`, and `DailyReport`) will then be crafted, all combined in `App.tsx`. I\'m starting the CSS for styling and plan on storing data in `localStorage`.\n\n\n**Implementing Data Structures**\n\nI\'m now writing `src/types.ts` to solidify the foundational data. I\'m defining `PaymentMethod` and `StudyType` enums, and the crucial `Transaction` interface, which includes fields for date, student details, payment method, and workflow states like `isReconciled` and `isInvoiced`. I\'m starting the `App.tsx` layout and state management, focusing on storing and loading transaction data via `localStorage`. The goal is a responsive design with a good-looking color palette, aiming for that \'clean enterprise SaaS\' feel, with blue as the primary color.\n\n\n**Adding Utility Functions**\n\nI\'ve added formatting helpers for currency and dates within `src/utils.ts`, including a function to generate unique IDs. I have `lucide-react` for a good set of icons. Next, I plan to break down `App.tsx` into smaller, more manageable components for improved readability and maintenance, aiming for a cleaner project structure.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 17
      nanos: 713399043
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
